The President's Cabinet meeting focused on national security issues, including the events in Egypt, Afghanistan, and Iraq. Secretary Clinton discussed the U.S.'s stance on opposing violence and supporting universal rights in Egypt. Secretary Napolitano provided an update on preparations for winter storms affecting the country. The President emphasized the need to tap into American creativity and innovation to outperform other countries in terms of education and building. He also discussed the tough choices that will be reflected in the 2012 Budget, aiming to reduce the deficit and reform the government to operate more efficiently.